China’s foreign ministry has said that the coronavirus pandemic that has infected more than 160,000 people globally has exposed the shortcomings in the global health system. Foreign ministry spokesman Geng Shuang told newsmen during a daily briefing on Wednesday that China calls on the international community to prioritise public health security. The ministry  stated the coronavirus pandemic has exposed the shortcomings of the global health system. According to Geng, China is calling on the international community to prioritise public health security. China has reported almost 81,000 cases of infection with 3,237 deaths so far, while the total number of people with the virus worldwide stands at almost 200,000 with a total of 8,000 fatalities. China, Italy, Iran, and Spain remain the countries hardest hit by the deadly infection.